# NotesApp — Windsurf Rules

## Tech Stack
- Java 25 LTS + Spring Boot 4.0.x
- Angular 21 (standalone, Signals, no NgModules)
- PostgreSQL 16 (Flyway migrations, tsvector FTS)
- JWT Auth (15 min access / 7 day refresh HttpOnly)
- TipTap rich text (ProseMirror JSON in JSONB column)
- STOMP WebSocket for real-time

## Architecture Rules

backend/
  controller/   → HTTP only, delegates to service
  service/      → all business logic lives here
  repository/   → Spring Data JPA interfaces only
  entity/       → JPA entities with Lombok
  security/     → JWT filter, UserDetails
  config/       → Spring configs (Security, WebSocket, CORS)
  dto/          → request/response objects (no entity exposure)
  exception/    → custom exceptions + @ControllerAdvice handler

frontend/src/app/
  core/         → singleton services (AuthService, WebSocketService, interceptors)
  features/     → feature modules (auth, notes)
  shared/       → reusable components, pipes, directives

## Guardrails
- API prefix: /api/v1/ always — iOS Phase 2 reuses this
- Flyway: add V{n+1}__name.sql, never modify existing migrations
- Tests: TestContainers for integration, mock repos for unit
- State: Angular Signals only (no RxJS BehaviorSubject for UI state)
- Rich text: JSONB column stores ProseMirror JSON, never HTML
- Tokens: access=JWT Bearer header, refresh=HttpOnly cookie
